# this file describes the screen fonts available to the interpreter
#
# the font name is that used by documents
#
# each screen font name comprises a prefix, a point size and a suffix. To be useful, a 
# range of sizes should be available.
# e.g.
#	family-cache/sans10.snf
#
#	family-cache/sans 	is the prefix
#	10			is one of the available point sizes
#	.snf			is the suffix
#
# a null suffix can be specified with ""
#
# if the prefix begins with a / it is taken to be an absolute path name
# if it does not, the $RALPAGELIB library name is prepended, so that fonts can be
# placed in the ralpage library.
#
# the resolution is in pixels per inch and describes the screen resolution that
# will display the font at the given point size.
#
# font name			prefix				suffix	resolution	format

Serif-Roman			adobe-cache/times		.snf	86		snf
Serif-Italic			adobe-cache/times		i.snf	86		snf
Serif-Bold			adobe-cache/times		b.snf	86		snf
Serif-BI			adobe-cache/times		bi.snf	86		snf

Sans-Roman			adobe-cache/helvetica		.snf	86		snf
Sans-Italic			adobe-cache/helvetica		i.snf	86		snf
Sans-Bold			adobe-cache/helvetica		b.snf	86		snf
Sans-BoldItalic			adobe-cache/helvetica		bi.snf	86		snf

